# Example config/review.env - post-implementation reviewer launch overrides.
# Copy to config/review.env (LOCAL, gitignored) and uncomment only what you change.
# An absent file means the pilot-verified defaults, shown here, apply.
# Full key reference: the header of bin/fm-review-launch.sh.
# The tracked review procedure uses the claude command for reviewer 2.
# Codex keys configure only the launcher's retained codex command, not the
# no-mistakes pipeline reviewer 1 selected by the operator's gate config.
#FM_REVIEW_CLAUDE_MODEL=claude-fable-5
#FM_REVIEW_CLAUDE_EFFORT=high
#FM_REVIEW_CODEX_MODEL=gpt-5.5
#FM_REVIEW_CODEX_EFFORT=high
# Per-repo guideline links baked into the reviewer prompts.
#FM_REVIEW_GUIDELINES=.review/guidelines.md
# Frontend guidelines apply when the PR contains frontend changes (e.g. a PR
# touching packages/app in the hightouch monorepo); set EMPTY to drop the
# frontend clause from the prompts for repos without one.
#FM_REVIEW_FRONTEND_GUIDELINES=.review/frontend.md
# Full flag-set overrides, word-split; each replaces its default flag set entirely.
#FM_REVIEW_CLAUDE_ARGS='--model claude-fable-5 --effort high --permission-mode auto'
#FM_REVIEW_CODEX_ARGS='--yolo --model gpt-5.5 -c model_reasoning_effort="high"'
